Step 1: Identify the quick assets. Quick assets include:
 • Cash on Hand = 2,179,154.14  
 • Bank Deposits = 2,952,150.00  
 • Interest Receivable = 9,881.70  
 • Accounts Receivable = 200,359.99  

Step 2: Calculate the total quick assets.  
 Total Quick Assets = 2,179,154.14 + 2,952,150.00 + 9,881.70 + 200,359.99  
  = 5,341,545.83  

Step 3: Identify current liabilities.  
 Total Current Liabilities = 5,042,389.63  

Step 4: Calculate the Quick Ratio.  
 Quick Ratio = Total Quick Assets / Total Current Liabilities  
  = 5,341,545.83 / 5,042,389.63  
  ≈ 1.06  

Thus, the Quick Ratio as of the end of the reporting period is approximately 1.06.
